    overview_calories: 'Calories',
    overview_recovery_status: 'Recovery Status',
    overview_recovery_status_tip: '**Readiness to train hard today**\n80-100% = Fresh \u2014 key sessions (intervals, long runs)\n60-80% = Moderate \u2014 steady work OK\n40-60% = Fatigued \u2014 keep it light\nBelow 40% = Rest day\n\n**How it works**\nEach workout generates a TRIMP score (duration x HR intensity).\nFatigue (ATL) = 7-day avg \u2014 rises fast, drops fast.\nFitness (CTL) = 42-day avg \u2014 builds slowly, decays slowly.\n\n**Formula**\nRecovery = 50 + (Fitness - Fatigue) x 0.7\nBaseline (no training) = 50%\nRest \u2192 fatigue drops faster \u2192 recovery rises\nHard training \u2192 fatigue spikes \u2192 recovery drops',
    overview_fitness: 'Fitness',
    overview_fatigue: 'Fatigue',
    overview_fitness_tip: '**Fitness (CTL)**\n42-day rolling average of daily TRIMP.\nYour aerobic "bank account".\n\n**Benchmarks**\n40-60 = Solid recreational base\n60-80 = Well-trained\n80+ = Competitive\n\nRises ~1-2 pts/week with consistent training.\nSharp drops = too much time off.',
    overview_fatigue_tip: '**Fatigue (ATL)**\n7-day rolling average of daily TRIMP.\nReflects recent training stress.\n\n**Reading it**\nAbove Fitness = loading phase, recovery drops\nBelow Fitness = rested, recovery rises\n\nAim for fatigue to exceed fitness only 2-3 weeks before a recovery week.',
    overview_recovery_tip: '**Before \u2192 After**\nBefore % = recovery going into the workout.\nAfter % = recovery remaining post-workout.\n\n**What the drop means**\nBig drop (80% \u2192 45%) = very demanding session\nSmall drop (75% \u2192 65%) = easy session\nBefore already < 50% = you should have rested',
    overview_recovery_training_load: 'Recovery & Training Load',
    overview_recovery_chart_tip: '**Chart Guide**\nGreen line (Recovery %) = daily readiness. Do key sessions above 70%.\nBlue dotted (Fitness/CTL) = should trend upward over weeks.\nRed dotted (Fatigue/ATL) = spikes after hard training.\nBlue bars = daily TRIMP (training load).\n\n**Healthy pattern**\n2-3 weeks of building fatigue, then a recovery week where fatigue drops and recovery rises.',
    overview_recent_workouts: 'Recent Workouts',
    overview_weekly_volume: 'Weekly Training Volume (hours)',
    overview_weekly_volume_tip: '**Weekly Volume**\nStacked hours per week by discipline.\n\n**What to look for**\nConsistent build-up with recovery weeks every 3-4 weeks.\nA good 70.3 build block increases volume ~10%/week.\nRecovery weeks should drop to ~60% of peak volume.',
